{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db1202df-ca80-444b-9da4-166d6da774e0","content":"Here's what to fix in each snippet for .NET 10:\n\n---\n\n**Form1.cs** — `ContextMenu` and `MenuItem` are **removed** in .NET 10 (obsolete-as-error since .NET 7, now fully gone). Replace with:\n\n```csharp\nvar menu = new ContextMenuStrip();\nmenu.Items.Add(new ToolStripMenuItem(\"Open\", image: null, OnOpen));\n```\n\n---\n\n**ImageProcessor.cs** — GDI+ historically threw `OutOfMemoryException` for invalid/corrupt image files. .NET 10 corrects this and now throws a more specific exception. Your `catch (OutOfMemoryException)` **will silently miss** bad-format errors. Fix:\n\n```csharp\ncatch (Exception ex) when (ex is OutOfMemoryException or IOException or ArgumentException)\n{\n    logger.LogError(ex, \"Invalid image format\");\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**MainWindow.xaml** — Two issues:\n\n1. **Empty `<Grid.ColumnDefinitions/>` / `<Grid.RowDefinitions/>`** — self-closing empty collections now explicitly clear defaults, which can cause layout issues. Remove them if unused.\n2. **`DynamicResource MissingKey`** — .NET 10 WPF raises a runtime `ResourceReferenceKeyNotFoundException` for missing keys instead of silently resolving to null. Either define the resource or add a `FallbackValue`:\n\n```xml\n<Grid>\n    <TextBlock Text=\"{DynamicResource MissingKey, FallbackValue='(none)'}\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\n---\n\n**Additional context you mentioned:**\n\n- **StatusStrip**: .NET 10 changes the default `RenderMode`. If you rely on the current look, explicitly set `RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.Professional` (or whichever you need).\n- **TreeView checkboxes**: State image handling changed in .NET 10 — checkbox toggling behavior may differ. Test and consider explicitly handling `BeforeCheck`/`AfterCheck` events if you see issues.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"edc240c0-d109-4445-99d9-6fe4c5a433c3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a .NET 9 Win